Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.93,0:03:18.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Your stomach hurts?! What a wet blanket!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.03,0:03:20.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just go to the bathroom already!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.79,0:03:39.09,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Strike three, you're out!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.09,0:03:41.92,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}When is one gonna make it to the stands?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.20,0:03:52.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna go watch the other people!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.27,0:03:53.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't bother them, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.51,0:03:54.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.67,0:04:00.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir. You can have mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.04,0:04:01.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.81,0:04:04.51,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}What a brown-noser...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.51,0:04:07.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Little boy. You should stay away, it's dangerous here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.28,0:04:10.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is far enough away, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.82,0:04:12.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.45,0:04:16.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Be sure to write off his driver repair as a section expense!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.49,0:04:18.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.81,0:04:33.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See? I told you it was dangerous...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.44,0:04:35.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No kidding...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.43,0:04:57.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice shot!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.33,0:04:59.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That one really flew!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.94,0:05:04.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You have Sunday's farewell contest in the bag!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.54,0:05:06.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.38,0:05:16.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That guy's done already?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.22,0:05:20.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He hit them at a pretty quick pace...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.06,0:05:24.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus he gave some of his golf balls to his boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.69,0:05:27.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What an obvious suck-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.51,0:05:40.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice shot!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.61,0:05:43.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's your driver.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.19,0:06:01.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.13,0:06:02.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.93,0:06:04.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Another miss?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.35,0:06:07.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep. 20 in a row...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.69,0:06:26.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.29,0:06:28.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.90,0:06:31.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop! Don't touch him!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.16,0:06:35.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's dead...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.76,0:06:37.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran! Call Inspector Megure!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.79,0:06:39.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.50,0:06:41.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What on earth happened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.74,0:06:44.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was most likely a bomb that exploded.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.57,0:06:46.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A bomb?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.18,0:06:53.08,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}This unique acrid smell... Black powder!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.52,0:06:56.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.79,0:06:57.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Call the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.92,0:07:00.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, there's a hospital just down the street!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.92,0:07:03.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! You're injured, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.33,0:07:06.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine! But we gotta get him to the hospital!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.23,0:07:07.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.47,0:07:20.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The deceased is Director Tachibana of Itsui Electronics...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.71,0:07:22.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.41,0:07:25.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Yasui, the section manager,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.21,0:07:27.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and this is Okubo and Minami.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.78,0:07:32.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We all work under Director Tachibana in Product Development.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.72,0:07:35.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you come here often?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.16,0:07:38.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, as it's close to the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.56,0:07:41.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But today was the director's last day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.06,0:07:42.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His last day?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.43,0:07:48.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was going to be promoted to head of the New York branch.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.80,0:07:53.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector. It appears it was black powder that was used.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.71,0:07:57.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And please come over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.15,0:08:01.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a fragment of the driver head.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.25,0:08:05.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And these are all ball fragments...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.75,0:08:07.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...but look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.86,0:08:09.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.66,0:08:11.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It appears to be a fuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.53,0:08:12.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.86,0:08:16.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...the bomb was inside the ball,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.37,0:08:21.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and set to explode when he hit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.60,0:08:24.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Precisely.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.78,0:08:32.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me, do all the golf balls here have red lines on them?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.11,0:08:34.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, blue lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.05,0:08:34.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue lines?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.02,0:08:38.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There are some there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.75,0:08:43.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. They have single blue lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.49,0:08:50.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means the red, crossed lines mark the bomb ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.63,0:08:55.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The question is, was this meant specifically for Director Tachibana,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.00,0:08:57.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,or was it a random act of terrorism...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.57,0:09:01.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it was meant for him specifically.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.18,0:09:03.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.85,0:09:12.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because all three of us here hated him enough to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.19,0:09:13.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.86,0:09:15.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What are you talking about, Minami?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.72,0:09:17.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.36,0:09:20.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We both had plenty of reason to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.76,0:09:26.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He had already taken credit for three of my product ideas,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.20,0:09:32.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and he always ignored you, no matter how many good ideas you had.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.34,0:09:35.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,N-Not me! I had no problems with the director!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.78,0:09:38.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Drop the act.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.38,0:09:43.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We all know he stole your girlfriend a long time ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.75,0:09:48.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No! She didn't get stolen! She dumped me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.26,0:09:53.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! I know who killed Director Tachibana, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.53,0:09:55.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You do, Mouri-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.36,0:09:58.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! First is the M.O...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.70,0:10:04.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer mixed the bomb ball with other balls in the machine,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.01,0:10:06.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so that the victim would hit it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.54,0:10:09.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The question then is,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.75,0:10:15.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,who got the golf balls for Director Tachibana?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.18,0:10:18.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was this Okubo person.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.53,0:10:28.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Meanwhile, Minami-{\i1}san{\i0} was in the restroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.06,0:10:31.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the Yasui guy was at his own machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.00,0:10:33.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So it was you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.40,0:10:35.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The kid's right, neither me nor Minami
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.94,0:10:38.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,touched the director's basket!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.57,0:10:42.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No one else could've put the bomb ball in there but you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.81,0:10:46.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's not necessarily the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.38,0:10:48.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no question that Minami-{\i1}san{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.45,0:10:51.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was far away from the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.89,0:10:55.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But not you, Yasui-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.09,0:11:00.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear you shared some of your golf bolls with the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.06,0:11:03.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That was...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.70,0:11:04.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.57,0:11:09.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you could have put the bomb ball in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.30,0:11:14.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait! If I did put it in there,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.41,0:11:19.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I could've died in the explosion too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.75,0:11:22.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The machines use a queue system;
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.25,0:11:27.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the last balls in are the last ones out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.02,0:11:32.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And you finished hitting before Tachibana-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.06,0:11:35.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Could that've been so you would finish
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.80,0:11:38.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,before he hit the bomb ball?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.27,0:11:42.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I just have a habit of hitting quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.27,0:11:45.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Okubo?! Minami?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.11,0:11:48.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then one other thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.94,0:11:52.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where were you during the explosion?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.38,0:11:56.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At this point, Okubo-{\i1}san{\i0} can also be removed as a suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.22,0:12:03.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason being that he was caught in the blast, as was Minami-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.79,0:12:08.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I believe you were by the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.13,0:12:10.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That was...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.43,0:12:18.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it because you saw the red-lined ball come up and took cover?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.51,0:12:22.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I went to order coffee!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.11,0:12:23.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Coffee?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.81,0:12:30.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! The director liked to drink coffee after he finished hitting!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.12,0:12:37.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So I always went and ordered it 10 minutes before he finished!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.33,0:12:38.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's telling the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.93,0:12:41.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We brew our coffee from beans,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.60,0:12:44.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so he always asks ahead of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.17,0:12:56.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it seems a bit too convenient that you were gone when it blew up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.95,0:12:58.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.28,0:13:00.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you think Yasui-{\i1}san{\i0} did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.42,0:13:01.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.62,0:13:03.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no question about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.52,0:13:04.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.89,0:13:07.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not the killer! Honest!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.52,0:13:12.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yasui-{\i1}san{\i0}. Just to be sure, may we check your things?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.16,0:13:15.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, that's fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.90,0:13:20.94,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}The old man's logic so far has been unusually consistent.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.94,0:13:24.74,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}But if Yasui-{\i1}san{\i0} really was the killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.98,0:13:30.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector! I found this in his bag!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.31,0:13:32.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is—!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.11,0:13:33.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.85,0:13:36.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is immutable proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.08,0:13:41.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You had a backup ready in case of a dud!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.49,0:13:43.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I didn't put that there!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.76,0:13:48.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Boy, what an incredibly simple case this was!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.26,0:13:51.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,For the great Kogoro Mouri,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.43,0:13:56.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,it was truly a piece of cake!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.71,0:13:58.74,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}This is way too simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.74,0:14:03.45,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Did Yasui-{\i1}san{\i0} not care if he got caught for killing Director Tachibana?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.45,0:14:07.95,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}No... There's something we're overlooking!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.95,0:14:11.04,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Something not even I noticed!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.99,0:14:15.69,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Huh? There's a ball on the tee...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.69,0:14:20.06,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Guess the old man missed it again!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.06,0:14:22.22,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Wait! I'm pretty sure I—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.20,0:14:31.97,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}I just assumed the old man hit the ball into a metal post.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.97,0:14:34.38,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}But he didn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.38,0:14:37.57,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Then what {\i1}was{\i0} that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.39,0:14:50.16,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Smells like explosives.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.16,0:14:54.03,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Which means {\i1}this{\i0} was the ball Director Tachibana hit,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.03,0:14:59.40,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}and that metallic sound was when it hit a post.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.40,0:15:03.24,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Then what were those bomb ball fragments?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.24,0:15:04.54,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.54,0:15:06.54,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}This is a trick the killer set!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.54,0:15:09.03,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}The real culprit is someone else!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.97,0:15:15.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We can talk down at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.10,0:15:17.00,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Oh no! I have to hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.41,0:15:22.67,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Alright! The usual method!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.91,0:15:30.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector! Please believe me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.35,0:15:32.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not the killer, honest!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.99,0:15:36.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, you're not the killer, Yasui-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.76,0:15:39.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.46,0:15:44.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Assuming the explosion happened when the victim hit a bomb ball
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.96,0:15:47.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was a mistake from the very start!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.30,0:15:49.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying, Mouri-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.70,0:15:53.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We found a ball fragment with a fuse at the scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.81,0:15:58.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we did. But Inspector, take a look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.58,0:16:02.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I found that ball by a metal post at the far end net.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.75,0:16:05.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not much, but it should smell of explosives.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.98,0:16:07.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.85,0:16:09.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When the bomb went off,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.96,0:16:12.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tachibana-{\i1}san{\i0} had hit not the red ball,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.32,0:16:17.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but that one with a blue stripe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.10,0:16:18.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hold on, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.66,0:16:21.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't get what you're saying!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.00,0:16:26.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer didn't place the bomb ball in Tachibana-{\i1}san{\i0}'s machine—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.64,0:16:29.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he planted it inside the driver head beforehand!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.81,0:16:30.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.94,0:16:35.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is where the killer was crafty.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.18,0:16:39.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If there were fragments left over after the explosion,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.18,0:16:47.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,everyone would simply assume it was the ball that blew up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.39,0:16:50.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! After the explosion,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.20,0:16:52.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the killer set down a pre-prepared fragment
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.16,0:16:53.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when given the opportunity!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.97,0:16:57.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But that would mean the killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.20,0:17:04.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yasui-{\i1}san{\i0}. I believe you mentioned the director's driver repair fees?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.18,0:17:09.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The shaft had a crack in it, so I had Minami send it for repairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.65,0:17:11.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Minami! You—!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.82,0:17:13.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Minami-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.99,0:17:16.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you have the driver repaired?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.52,0:17:17.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.99,0:17:20.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We also do club repair here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.56,0:17:22.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In what way did you repair it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.93,0:17:32.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I felt it best to turn it into a carbon shaft club.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.07,0:17:37.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That club was given to the director by the current CEO 15 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.18,0:17:40.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So the director was very attached to it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.61,0:17:44.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So it was an old-fashioned wood head?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.52,0:17:47.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, when did you return the repaired club to Minami-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.69,0:17:50.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I returned it to him two nights ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.59,0:17:52.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Two nights ago?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.69,0:17:56.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But you gave it to the director this morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.09,0:18:05.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning the driver was in your possession for an entire day and night.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.10,0:18:09.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let us look back at your actions today.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.24,0:18:11.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Immediately after arriving here...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.31,0:18:14.65,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}What? Your stomach hurts?! What a wet blanket!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.65,0:18:18.55,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Just go to the bathroom already!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.55,0:18:24.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was just one of the steps of his plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.42,0:18:29.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you perhaps usually have Minami-{\i1}san{\i0} get your golf balls
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.96,0:18:35.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and have him put ten or so in Director Tachibana's own machine?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.53,0:18:37.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.47,0:18:42.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This time, he purposely said his stomach hurt and fled to the restroom
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.77,0:18:45.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to pass that role onto you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.61,0:18:51.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Moreover, he planned to narrow down the suspects to just you,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.18,0:18:55.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,by having you be away from the scene the instant of the explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.25,0:19:00.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He managed this by giving him the driver
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.36,0:19:06.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,just as you left for coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.73,0:19:08.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.97,0:19:12.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to completely clear himself of suspicion,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.80,0:19:19.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he stood nearby so that he would get caught in the explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.38,0:19:20.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.31,0:19:23.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Think about where Minami-{\i1}san{\i0} was injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.65,0:19:27.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okubo-{\i1}san{\i0} received injuries to almost his entire body,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.29,0:19:31.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,yet he only received injuries outside his left elbow and leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.82,0:19:33.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why his left side?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.99,0:19:36.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why outside, and not inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.86,0:19:39.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's because moments before the explosion,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.00,0:19:41.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he quickly covered his eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.67,0:19:44.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,with his left arm and hid behind a pillar.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.61,0:19:51.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Minami-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.34,0:19:56.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Today was the last chance you had to kill Director Tachibana,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.38,0:19:58.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,as he was about to move to New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.95,0:20:06.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But wasn't using the driver only you could've had in the last two days
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.53,0:20:11.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,as the murder weapon a bit careless on your part?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.60,0:20:15.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've always hated the director.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.03,0:20:18.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The director who would never acknowledge my skill,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.30,0:20:23.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and Manager Yasui, who never did anything but suck up to him...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.48,0:20:29.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So I plotted to kill the director and have him take the fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.05,0:20:34.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And you didn't care if anyone else died in the explosion?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.59,0:20:38.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Had this golf range been crowded, even more people would've—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.39,0:20:41.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't give a damn about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.93,0:20:48.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.74,0:20:57.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think he really meant that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.45,0:20:59.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.11,0:21:01.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, he...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.51,0:21:04.25,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Little boy. You should stay away, it's dangerous here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.25,0:21:08.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think he said that so I wouldn't get caught in the explosion!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.62,0:21:09.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.96,0:21:17.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows, he might've actually been a nice person who lost his way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.60,0:21:20.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.93,0:21:23.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-We're late for school!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.08,0:22:56.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}"1st Annual Nichiuri TV Pro-Amateur Charity Golf Tournament"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.07,0:23:06.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yoko-{\i1}chan{\i0}! Nice shot!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.77,0:23:08.01,Narration,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}The following Sunday,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.01,0:23:10.58,Narration,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}the old man entered the golf tournament
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.58,0:23:15.11,Narration,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}on the condition that he be on Yoko Okino's team.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.11,0:23:18.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yoko-{\i1}chan{\i0} was a bit unsteady, but it was a nice shot!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.35,0:23:21.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next up is the famous detective, Kogoro Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.82,0:23:24.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0}! You can do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.49,0:23:27.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.69,0:23:29.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is Dad gonna be alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.54,0:23:31.86,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.70,0:23:38.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yikes...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.47,0:23:43.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Gimme a break!
